data.enText: to change sth slightly to make it more suitable for a new set of conditions or to make it work better

data.chText: 当心急转弯并相应调整车速。
data.enText: Watch out for sharp bends and adjust your speed accordingly.

data.chText: 这个按钮是调节音量的。
data.enText: This button is for adjusting the volume.

data.chText: 要根据听众的年龄使用相应的语言。
data.enText: Adjust your language to the age of your audience.
to get used to a new situation by changing the way you behave and/or think

data.chText: 她过了一段时间才适应独自生活。
data.enText: It took her a while to adjust to living alone.

data.chText: 过了一会儿他的眼睛习惯了黑暗。
data.enText: After a while his eyes adjusted to the dark.

data.chText: 你将很快适应学生生活。
data.enText: You'll quickly adjust yourself to student life.
to move sth slightly so that it looks neater or feels more comfortable

data.chText: 他捋平头发，整了整领带。
data.enText: He smoothed his hair and adjusted his tie.

simple_means.memory_skill: ad 做…或加强 + just 正确 → 使正确 → 调整

ex.chText: 过一会儿你的眼睛就能适应黑暗。
ex.enText: Your eyes will accommodate to the darkness after a while.

ex.chText: 她不得不使自己适应新的工作。
ex.enText: She had to accommodate to a new job.
He adapted to the new school.

ex.chText: 鲍勃改装了旧汽车，这样他的儿子便能使用。
ex.enText: Bob adapted his old car so his son could use it.

synonyms.bx: 强调改变现有条件以适应新的情况。

ex.chText: 他的眼睛还没有适应黑暗。
ex.enText: His eyes have't adjusted to the darkness yet.
Kids are quite good at adjusting.

synonyms.bx: 指稍微调整以适应特定工作或新的情况，调整幅度没有 adapt 大，常后接介词 to。

tr: adapt or conform oneself to new or different conditions
example: We must adjust to the bad economic situation

tr: alter or regulate so as to achieve accuracy or conform to a standard
example: correct the alignment of the front wheels
Adjust your eyes to the darkness

tr: place in a line or arrange so as to be parallel or straight
example: align the car with the curb
align the sheets of paper on the table

tr: decide how much is to be paid on an insurance claim

value.def: When you adjust to a new situation, you get used to it by changing your behaviour or your ideas.

example.ex: We have been preparing our fighters to adjust themselves to civil society...
example.tran: 我们一直在培训我们的战士，以使他们适应普通的社会生活。

example.ex: I felt I had adjusted to the idea of being a mother very well...
example.tran: 我感到自己已经完全接受了当妈妈的想法。

example.ex: It has been hard to adjust but now I'm getting satisfaction from my work.
example.tran: 适应虽然艰难，但是现在我已逐渐从工作中获得了满足。

value.tran: 改变（行为或观点）以适应;调节;习惯

value.def: If you adjust something, you change it so that it is more effective or appropriate.

example.ex: To attract investors, Panama has adjusted its tax and labour laws.
example.tran: 为吸引投资者，巴拿马调整了税法和劳动法。

value.def: If you adjust something such as your clothing or a machine, you correct or alter its position or setting.

example.ex: She adjusted her head scarf fussily...
example.tran: 她小题大做地整了整头巾。

example.ex: Liz adjusted her mirror and then edged the car out of its parking bay.
example.tran: 莉兹调了调后视镜，将车子挪出了停车位。

value.tran: 整理（衣服）；校正，校准（机器）

value.def: If you adjust your vision or if your vision adjusts, the muscles of your eye or the pupils alter to cope with changes in light or distance.

example.ex: He stopped to try to adjust his vision to the faint starlight...
example.tran: 他停下脚步试着让眼睛适应微弱的星光。

example.ex: We stood in the doorway until our eyes adjusted...
example.tran: 我们站在门口直到眼睛适应了光线的变化。

example.ex: It was a few moments before his eyes became adjusted to the bright glare of the sun.
example.tran: 过了一会儿，他的眼睛才适应了刺眼的阳光。
